03/18/76   set_acl, sa

Function:  sets the access control lists (ACLs) of files.


Syntax:  sa file_name mode1 {User_id1 ... modeN User_idN}


Arguments:
file_name  name of file; star convention can be used.
modei  access mode; can be any or all of the letters rew (or
 null, n, or "" for null access).
User_idi  access control name of the form Person_id.Project_id.tag.
 If the last modei has no following User_id, user's Person_id and
 Project_id are assumed.
